cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.CV 

This paper is primarily concerned with training recurrent neural networks as goal-oriented dialog agents using reinforcement learning, which falls under the category of natural language processing and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of policy gradients and positive memory retention, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The experiments involve a visual object discovery game, which could be related to robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV).
